The paper discusses a regularization technique for deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of convolutional neural networks is also mentioned, indicating a focus on computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other possible sub-categories include cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the proposed technique may have applications in natural language processing tasks.
